This paper deals with a variant of the classic bin packing problem, which is a well-known problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces novel techniques for dealing with small items, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of concave functions in the cost structure of the problem suggests that the paper could be relevant to the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the development of an approximation algorithm with a guaranteed approximation ratio suggests that the paper could be relevant to the sub-category of numerical analysis (cs.NA).
